text: Nicole [ ni-kohl; French nee-kawl ] is a female given name of Greek origin. It means "victorious people". It is the French female version of the boy's name Nicholas. There are many variants for this female name. Famous persons going by the name include Nicole Sullivan and Nicole Kidman. The name is being used for tropical storms or hurricanes in Atlantic Basin. This name was ranked #340 on the US Popular Names in 2021. == People == * Nicole Kidman, Australian- American actress, producer, and model * Nicole Scherzinger, American singer, songwriter, dancer, actress, and television personality * Nicole Jung, South Korean-American singer ==References== Category:Given names
